title: Distribution and Genetic Profiles of Campylobacter in Commercial Broiler Production from Breeder to Slaughter in Thailand
summary: This study investigates the distribution and genetic diversity of Campylobacter species throughout the commercial broiler production chain in Thailand, from breeder flocks to slaughter facilities. Results demonstrate significant genetic variation across production stages, providing insights for targeted intervention strategies to reduce Campylobacter contamination in poultry products.

title: Genetic dissection of seed-iron and zinc concentrations in chickpea
summary: This research performs a comprehensive genetic analysis to identify quantitative trait loci (QTL) controlling iron and zinc concentrations in chickpea seeds. The findings reveal multiple genomic regions associated with micronutrient accumulation, offering valuable markers for breeding programs aimed at developing biofortified chickpea varieties.
